sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70594
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A RFC12 compatible part that simply codes for two stop codons. This part does not have any degradation tag.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made with synthetic oligos: 5' AATTC GCGGCGC T ACTAGT TAATAA GCTAGC A GCGGCCG CTGCA 3' 5' GCGGCCGCTGCTAGC TTATTA ACTAGTAGCGCCGC G 3'
Note that both primers were ordered phosphorylated. An alternative is to phosphorylate the primers yourself with a kinase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Joseph Lynch

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Sequence excerpt from the pET-28a-c(+) series of vectors.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Thrombin c
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the amino acid sequence LVPRGS. This site is recognized by Thrombin, which will cleave the Arg-Gly peptide bond.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mDNMT1(731
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Mus musculus; codon-optimized for E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the amino acides 731 through 1602 of DNA (cytosine-5)-methyltransferase 1 (DNMT1) from ''Mus musculus'', containing the BAH1, BAH2, and methyltransferase domains [[{{PAGENAME}}:Design#References|[1]]]. It is codon-optimized for ''E. coli''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Constantin Ahlmann-Eltze, Charlotte Bunne, Magdalena Büscher, Jan Gleixner, Max Horn, Anna Huhn, Nils Klughammer, Jakob Kreft, Elisabeth Schäfer, Carolin Schmelas, Silvan Schmitz, Max Waldha
